'''''BlackJack Academy''''' is a 1988 video game published by [[MicroIllusions]].

==Gameplay==
''BlackJack Academy'' is a game in which the player learns how to play [[blackjack]] through a simulation in a [[casino]] environment.<ref name="CGW43"/>

==Reception==
Roy Wagner reviewed the game for ''[[Computer Gaming World]]'', and stated that "This program is a good example of software that can be used for recreational fun, serious study, and possibly financial profit (or loss). The graphics and sound are at a quality level. The user interface is excellent. If you like playing blackjack or want to learn more about the game, this program is for you."<ref name="CGW43">{{cite magazine |last=Wagner |first=Roy |title=BlackJack Academy |magazine=Computer Gaming World |date=January 1988 |volume=1 |issue=43 |pages=54}}</ref>

